  "slug": "pumpkin-bread-american",
  "title": "American pumpkin bread",
  "subtitle": "Spiced quick bread with tinned pumpkin",
  "excerpt": "A moist, deeply spiced American quick bread made with tinned pumpkin puree. Warm with cinnamon, ginger, and nutmeg. One bowl, forty-minute bake. No mixer required.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Pumpkin bread is an American quick-bread tradition, documented in domestic cookery from the mid-twentieth century. The formula uses tinned pumpkin puree rather than fresh pumpkin, a practical American pantry ingredient. The spicing follows the pumpkin-pie spice profile: cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, and clove.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The bread gets its distinctive moist crumb from the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "pumpkin puree",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpaehewm0000s0v4e99peggc"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ", which contributes both water and pectin. It bakes low and slow for an hour, the interior stays dense and moist while the crust sets and cracks along the top in the usual quick-bread way.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
